    {
        "content": "<p>The main application of <code>tauto</code> itself does nothing (in your case) but <code>tauto</code> calls <code>solve_by_elim</code> after running, which solves the goal.</p>",
        "id": 464898787,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1724531588
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"690858\">Daniel Weber</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/236449-Program-verification/topic/theorem.20on.20ranges/near/464872723\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There seems to be a lot of missing API for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Std.Range#doc\">docs#Std.Range</a> which causes this</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Perhaps it'll be added to Lean's standard library in the future.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110087\">Kim Morrison</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/348111-batteries/topic/ten.20unproved.20string.20theorems/near/445030062\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There will be more news coming about this later, and when a design document is available we will post it, but it is possible there will be a radical overhaul of the String library (indeed, even the definition of String), so I would hesitate to encourage significant work on String at the moment as it may become obsolete (even to the point of not being able to meaningfully migrate results).</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 464912011,
        "sender_full_name": "Bulhwi Cha",
        "timestamp": 1724542802
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110087\">Kim Morrison</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/348111-batteries/topic/ten.20unproved.20string.20theorems/near/465414340\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Unfortunately overhauling <code>String</code> by the FRO has fallen back to medium priority, and in particular no one is actively working on it now.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I'm afraid Lean's still not ready to provide enough APIs for strings.</p>",
        "id": 465587789,
        "sender_full_name": "Bulhwi Cha",
        "timestamp": 1724801931
    }
